---
/**
 * kolu.dev/tui — quick reference for the kolu-tui CLI (beta).
 *
 * Deliberately UNLISTED: linked from nowhere on the site, excluded from the
 * sitemap (astro.config.mjs), and noindex'd below — it's a URL you hand to
 * someone trying the beta, not a navigation destination. Flip those three
 * switches together when the CLI graduates.
 */
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const commands = [
  {
    cmd: "kolu-tui list",
    flags: "--json",
    what: "One row per live terminal — id · pid · idle · cmd · cwd. --json emits a top-level array for jq.",
  },
  {
    cmd: "kolu-tui snapshot <id>",
    flags: "",
    what: "Print a terminal's current scrollback as plain text and exit — built for piping and grepping (a trailer line goes to stderr, so stdout stays clean).",
  },
  {
    cmd: "kolu-tui attach <id>",
    flags: "--escape <char>",
    what: "Take the terminal over, full screen. Raw passthrough — every keystroke and chord reaches the inner program; your window size follows along. Detach with the escape below.",
  },
];

const escapes = [
  { keys: "~.", what: "detach — kolu-tui exits, kolu-server keeps the terminal; re-attach anytime" },
  { keys: "~~", what: "send one literal ~ to the shell" },
  { keys: "~?", what: "show this escape help" },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="kolu-tui"
  description="kolu-tui — list, snapshot, and attach to your kolu terminals from the shell."
>
  <meta name="robots" content="noindex" slot="head" />

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 pt-20 md:pt-28 pb-10">
    {/* Warning orange (--color-brand-amber), NOT the site accent: the
        `amber` token is the purple brand accent, and an alpha warning must
        read as a warning. */}
    <div
      class="mb-8 flex items-start gap-3 border border-brand-amber/50 bg-brand-amber/10 rounded-lg px-4 py-3 max-w-xl"
    >
      <svg
        class="mt-0.5 h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-brand-amber"
        viewBox="0 0 24 24"
        fill="none"
        stroke="currentColor"
        stroke-width="2"
        stroke-linecap="round"
        stroke-linejoin="round"
        aria-hidden="true"
      >
        <path d="M10.29 3.86 1.82 18a2 2 0 0 0 1.71 3h16.94a2 2 0 0 0 1.71-3L13.71 3.86a2 2 0 0 0-3.42 0z"
        ></path>
        <line x1="12" y1="9" x2="12" y2="13"></line>
        <line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12.01" y2="17"></line>
      </svg>
      <p class="mono text-sm text-ink leading-relaxed">
        <span class="text-brand-amber font-semibold">alpha</span> — kolu-tui is
        an early preview. Commands, flags, and output formats{" "}
        <span class="text-ink">will change</span> before it's finalized for
        production use; don't script against it yet.
      </p>
    </div>
    <p class="eyebrow mb-4">the terminal client · alpha</p>
    <h1 class="display text-[3.2rem] md:text-[4.2rem] text-ink">
      kolu, without<br />the <span class="text-amber">browser</span>.
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-6 text-ink-dim max-w-xl leading-relaxed">
      <code class="mono text-ink">kolu-tui</code> talks to{" "}
      <span class="text-ink">kolu-server</span> — the process that{" "}
      <code class="mono text-ink">nix run github:juspay/kolu</code> starts and
      your browser points at — over a local unix socket, and drives the very
      same terminals the browser shows: list them, dump their scrollback, or
      attach and type. The CLI comes and goes; the server keeps owning the
      terminals.
    </p>
    <p class="mono text-ink-faint text-sm leading-relaxed mt-7">
      // start the server first, then:{" "}
      <code class="text-ink">nix run github:juspay/kolu#kolu-tui -- list</code>
      <br />
      <span class="text-ink-faint">
        the home-manager module installs it next to the server automatically.
      </span>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 pb-14">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-5">commands</p>
    {
      commands.map((c) => (
        <div class="border-t border-rule py-5 grid md:grid-cols-[16rem_1fr] gap-2 md:gap-8">
          <div>
            <code class="mono text-ink text-sm">{c.cmd}</code>
            {c.flags && (
              <div class="mono text-ink-faint text-xs mt-1">{c.flags}</div>
            )}
          </div>
          <p class="text-ink-dim text-sm leading-relaxed">{c.what}</p>
        </div>
      ))
    }
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 pb-14">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-5">detaching — the ssh model</p>
    <p class="text-ink-dim text-sm leading-relaxed max-w-xl">
      While attached, <em>nothing</em> is intercepted except a{" "}
      <code class="mono text-ink">~</code> typed at the start of a line
      (right after Enter — session start counts too). Mid-line tildes, every
      Ctrl chord, and pasted text all pass straight through, so the program
      inside never loses a key.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-5">
      {
        escapes.map((e) => (
          <div class="border-t border-rule py-3.5 grid grid-cols-[5rem_1fr] gap-6">
            <code class="mono text-amber text-sm">{e.keys}</code>
            <p class="text-ink-dim text-sm leading-relaxed">{e.what}</p>
          </div>
        ))
      }
    </div>
    <p class="mono text-ink-faint text-sm leading-relaxed mt-5">
      // ~ clashes (nested ssh?) — rebind it:{" "}
      <code class="text-ink">kolu-tui attach &lt;id&gt; --escape %</code>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 pb-24">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-5">fine print</p>
    <ul class="text-ink-dim text-sm leading-relaxed max-w-xl space-y-3">
      <li>
        The socket lives at{" "}
        <code class="mono text-ink">$XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/kolu/pty-host.sock</code>{" "}
        (falling back to{" "}
        <code class="mono text-ink">/tmp/kolu-$UID/pty-host.sock</code>) and
        appears when kolu-server boots. Point at a non-default server with{" "}
        <code class="mono text-ink">--pty-host-socket &lt;path&gt;</code> —
        same flag on the server.
      </li>
      <li>
        Detach is <span class="text-ink">client-side</span>: the CLI can come
        and go while the server holds the terminal. And since the pty-host
        daemon landed, restarting kolu-server{" "}
        <span class="text-ink">keeps its terminals too</span> — they live in a
        surviving daemon the restarted server reconnects to, by id, with
        scrollback intact.
      </li>
      <li>
        When the program inside exits, kolu-tui exits with the same code.
        An unreachable server is a one-line error, never a hang.
      </li>
      <li>
        Next up: <code class="mono text-ink">spawn</code> and{" "}
        <code class="mono text-ink">kill</code> — creating and ending
        terminals from the shell.
      </li>
      <li>
        The full design — architecture, phasing, and the decisions behind the
        escape model — lives in the{" "}
        <a
          href="https://htmlpreview.github.io/?https://github.com/juspay/kolu/blob/master/docs/atlas/dist/pty-daemon-tui.html"
          class="text-amber hover:underline"
          rel="noopener">kolu-tui atlas note</a
        >.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
